Homer MQTT-protocol

Devices are controlled by publishing values and subscribing to 
/devices/$devicename/$attribute
	
For each attribute, the device has to publish a type to 
/devices/$devicename/$attribute/type

Currently possible values for type are: "switch", "range"

Additionally, each device has to publish an attribute of name "power" with type "switch" that controlls 
it's general power status


Sensors publish to 
/sensors/sensorname